Class PopulationDynamics

java.lang.Object
org.jscience.biology.ecology.PopulationDynamics
public class PopulationDynamics extends Object
Population dynamics models for ecology.

Provides:

  • Exponential growth
  • Logistic growth (Verhulst equation)
  • Lotka-Volterra predator-prey model
  • Competition models

* @author Silvere Martin-Michiellot
Since:
1.0
Author:
Gemini AI (Google DeepMind)

    • lotkaVolterra

      public static double[][] lotkaVolterra(double prey, double predator, double alpha, double beta, double delta, double gamma, double timeStep, int steps)
      Solving Lotka-Volterra predator-prey equations using Euler method. dx/dt = alpha*x - beta*x*y (Prey) dy/dt = delta*x*y - gamma*y (Predator)
      Parameters:
      prey - Initial prey population
      predator - Initial predator population
      alpha - Prey growth rate
      beta - Predation rate
      delta - Predator reproduction rate
      gamma - Predator death rate
      timeStep - dt
      steps - Number of steps to simulate
      Returns:
      [steps][2] array where [i][0] is prey, [i][1] is predator

    • preyEquilibrium

      public static double preyEquilibrium(double gamma, double delta)
      Lotka-Volterra equilibrium - prey population. N* = gamma/delta

    • predatorEquilibrium

      public static double predatorEquilibrium(double alpha, double beta)
      Lotka-Volterra equilibrium - predator population. P* = alpha/beta

    • competitionGrowthRate

      public static double competitionGrowthRate(double n1, double n2, double r1, double k1, double alpha12)
      Competitive exclusion - Lotka-Volterra competition. dN1/dt = r1*N1 * (K1 - N1 - alpha12*N2) / K1
      Parameters:
      n1 - species 1 population
      n2 - species 2 population
      r1 - growth rate of species 1
      k1 - carrying capacity of species 1
      alpha12 - competition coefficient (effect of N2 on N1)
      Returns:
      growth rate of species 1
